<!--
Add this block to your repo's AGENTS.md so Codex routes itself to its fleet
role. Codex reads AGENTS.md automatically.
-->

## Orca Fleet Mode (fable-fleet) — Codex role routing

This applies ONLY when you are dispatched as part of a fleet run.

- **Main coder** — when a dispatch spec references `orca/roles/` or a plan under
  `feature-research/`, you are the bulk implementer. Read
  `orca/roles/codex-coder.md` and comply. The spec names the plan and the task
  id.

You implement your assigned task only, write your `audit-<task-id>.md`, and
signal completion with `worker_done`. You never orchestrate, never expand
scope, and never touch files outside your task's Files-touched list.

If a dispatch spec names a role file, that file wins over this routing.
